Description: St Sebastian, crowned by an angel, standing between St Anthony on the left, holding open book and bell, and St Roch on the right, healed by an angel; the plate is unfinished. c.1555 Engraving
Curator's comments: Eisler proposes to date this plate c.1554, when the great plague struck Burgundy.
Bibliographic references: Eisler 1977 / The Master of the Unicorn, the Life and Work of Jean Duvet (70)
Associated names: Representation of: St Antony of Egypt
